  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Role</strong></u><br />To be responsible for developing new F&B business while supportingF&B operations.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>To market and promote Café Lodge’s signature dishes and menu.</li><li>To explore, identify and develop new business opportunity for Café Lodge. </li><li>To build and maintain good client relationship and rapport.</li><li>To actively brainstorming or creative ideas in improving F&B menu and services to clients.</li><li>To follow-up on enquiries and complaints promptly when referred to.</li><li>To finalize all bookings and maximize all revenue potential by upselling. </li><li>To conduct restaurant visitations for potential clients.</li><li>To deliver professional and quality F&B services to clients.</li><li>To submit weekly, monthly, quarterly & annual sales reports.  </li><li>To attend in-house F&B reception services when scheduled. </li><li>To manage all F&B assets and inventory.</li><li>To be responsible for Service quality, Customers feedback and handling of after sales service that includes loyalty programs.          </li><li>To carry out any other duties and responsibilities that may be assigned from time to time by the Management.<br /><u><strong></strong></u><br /><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></li></ul><ul><li>Minimum GCE ‘O’ level, Higher NITEC in Hospitality Operations preferred.</li><li>At least 1 year of working experience in Food & Beverage or Hospitalitysector. </li><li>Proficiency in computer skills (Microsoft Excel, Microsoft Word).</li><li>Shift works including weekends and public holidays.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Cheerful and pleasant personality.</li><li>Strong communication skills</li><li>A good team player and demonstrates high initiative</li></ul>",
